BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
A lot could be simplified on each side before continuing, by distributing and combining like terms.

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
3(x+2)-8\amp=(5x+4)-2(x+1)\\
3x+6-8\amp=5x+4-2x-2\\
3x-2\amp=3x+2
\end{aligned}
```]

From here, we subtract [`3x`] from each side:

[```\newcommand{\subtractright}[1]{{\highlight{{{}-#1}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
3x-2\subtractright{3x}\amp=3x+2\subtractright{3x}\\
-2\amp=2
\end{aligned}
```]

As the equation [`-2=2`] is outright false, there is no solution to this equation.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

